news.title: Sunteck Realty posts net loss of Rs 13.94 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: Sunteck Realty's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 36.22 crore, a dip of 58.74 per cent from Rs 87.79 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: China Evergrande revises terms of proposed restructuring
news.para: Evergrande, which is at the centre of China's property sector debt crisis, said late last month that its billionaire founder was being investigated over unspecified crimes.

news.title: OfficeBanao to reach Rs 200 crore order book by FY24, says CEO
news.para: Company has received orders from Jaipur, Panchkula, Sonipat, Jamnagar, Indore, Aurangabad, Indore, Kolkata, Bhuvneshwar, Patna and Moradabad among others.

news.title: Delhi: 40% of unsold flats gone in three months, DDA gets Rs 506 crore
news.para: While full payment has been received for 1,249 flats, the transaction is in process for the others. So far, DDA has generated a revenue of Rs 506 crore under the scheme.

news.title: Nashik civic body to reintroduce industrial slab for property tax from next financial year
news.para: Tambe, while talking to TOI, said the municipal commissioner has agreed to implement the government’s guidelines of recovering property tax from the industries under the industrial slab.

news.title: MICL Group acquires additional 12.5% stake in Atmosphere Realty for Rs 12.5 crore
news.para: MICL Group has acquired 3,125 equity shares (representing 12.50% of the paid uo equity share capital) of ARPL.

news.title: VDA registers FIR against Varanasi-based real estate firm
news.para: VDA acted on the directions and an official communication issued by the Lucknow-headquartered investigation wing of the Income Tax (IT) department and sent a complaint to the Varanasi Police against the company.

news.title: Udaipur Cement Works doubles its clinker capacity to three million tonnes per annum
news.para: Udaipur Cement Works has commissioned its clinkerisation unit of 1.50 million tonnes per annum (MTPA) at Udaipur. With this, it has doubled its clinker capacity from 1.50 MTPA to 3 MTPA.

news.title: Punjab: Brick kiln owners unhappy with order on blending biomass pellets & coal
news.para: ​Last year, the government directed brick kilns to blend biomass pellets in coal in such a way that the pellets make up for 20% of the mix. However, kiln owners have suggest that they be allowed to use the pellets as mud fuel and an upper price cap be imposed on the pellets.

news.title: Kajaria Ceramics' net profit up 60.87% in Q2 FY24
news.para: Kajaria Ceramics' total consolidated income stood at Rs 1,129.89 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 4.10 per cent from Rs 1,085.39 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Maharashtra cabinet okays Rs 25 crore for Thane cluster redevelopment plan
news.para: The money was sanctioned from the Mahatma Phule Backward Class Development Corporation by the social justice department. Chief minister Eknath Shinde holds the social justice portfolio and hails from Thane.

news.title: CIDCO approves six-year construction period from plot possession for Navi Mumbai Airport affected people
news.para: CIDCO has granted the extended period due to the project's national importance and to ensure smooth development of the plots. If construction is not completed within the six-year period, land holders will need to apply for an extension.

news.title: Delhi LG nod for acquisition of land for metro corridors
news.para: Hurdles in the way of "long-pending" and critical metro lines in the city include the Aerocity-Tughlaqabad, Janakpuri West-RK Ashram, and Rahat Ganj-Roshanara Road-Pul Bangash corridors, have been cleared, they said.

news.title: Ahmedabad: No housing in new Sabarmati riverfront plan
news.para: The revised development plan of the riverfront, which now spans 19.74 lakh square metres, is 75,000 square metres less than the original plan.

news.title: Derabassi builder, revenue staffer under SIT lens in fake NOCs scam
news.para: Their names were revealed by the arrested accused — Gulshan Kumar of ward number 18 and Suresh Kumar of ward number 15 in Derabassi — during their custodial interrogation.

news.title: About 1.25 crore families to get ownership rights of land by Dec 2023: Uttar Pradesh CM
news.para: Uttar Pradesh Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath said, "75 lakh families in the state were given possession of the land where they reside. By December 2023, 1.25 lakh families of Uttar Pradesh will be given ownership rights of leased land under the PM SVAMITVA Yojana."

news.title: WeWork's chief operating officer to step down
news.para: WeWork has been in turmoil ever since its plans to go public in 2019 imploded as investors worried over its hefty losses and began to doubt its business model of taking long-term leases and renting them for the short term.

news.title: Gurugram: 50 illegal colonies demolished in DTCP crackdown
news.para: District town planner Binesh Kumar identified 14 illegal colonies in Sohna and Bhondsi area which were built violating the Haryana Urban Development Act, 1975. These colonies were being developed on 41 acres of agricultural land.
